A BHP sign adorns the side of their headquarters in Melbourne. AFP/William West JOHANNESBURG - Diversified miner BHP said it will pay out a record R73,4-billion in interim dividends. In the past six months, the company’s profit rose by 17 percent. READ: Mining giant BHP says coal outlook 'challenged' BHP said it's hopeful of a global economic recovery in light of vaccine rollouts and stimulus efforts and foresees a sustained demand for commodities. It said it expects continuing growth in demand for energy, metals, and fertilisers. Profit from operations rose 17 percent to R140-billion with COVID-19 costing it over R6,3-million before tax, due to increased security, health and hygiene costs.